<br>
“Of course.”<br>
<br>
Jorloc smiled “So tell me the short version, we haven’t all day.”<br>
<br>
“When the gods met in council to populate Norrath, they excluded Innoruuk from the meeting.  In righteous anger he seized the King and Queen of the Elves and molded them into a finer race of elves, his children the Teir’Dal.  When Innoruuk returned them to their former kingdom, they set upon a conquest for all Norrath until the cowards of Tunare betrayed those loyal to the crown.  Innoruuk led his children deep into the earth and saved us from destruction.”<br>
<br>
Jorloc’s tone was dry. “Thus so.  And so the city of Neriak was created.  This is the history all children are passed down.  There is however, more to this story…” At that Jorloc took a slow drink of a wine so dark that Kalial could not determine its true color.  <br>
<br>
“Our people have forgotten the small force of Teir’Dal that left this city over four hundred years ago.  Led by Duke Xxo’Kal, a force of eight Indigo champions, two priests of our Father and one great Necromancer who was only known as Vek’Na set forth to increase the hold we had in the deep places of the world.  To expand our power on Tunaria.  To rebuild our Kingdom!  You see boy, Xxo’Kal was the direct descendant to the throne and next in the succession.  After the War of the Broken Crown, he not only yearned to rebuild our mighty empire, but feared for his life from others who might dream of wearing the next crown.  So, he gathered a small force of our greatest and slipping into the black of night they traveled to new lands in search of a stronghold from which to wreak our vengeance!”<br>
<br>
Kalial sat in silence for a moment and mulled over this information.  Then he just looked at his father expectantly and awaited further comment.<br>
<br>
“So you’re no fool after all.  Good.  Listen closely son; for few know this and fewer still should ever speak about it until the time comes.  Xxo’Kal was indeed forgotten here in Neriak as we struggled for survival so close to those races that would destroy us.  It would seem that new information leads us to believe that Xxo’Kal was successful and his outpost thrived.  Choosing only to tap those he felt trustworthy, he summoned many of our people to him in secrecy to populate and build his new kingdom.  Ha!  If only the fools had paid attention, they might have noticed them slipping away from us, never to return…  The filthy humans have a saying that is quite fitting about hindsight being perfect vision.  No matter now.  So boy, do you understand what I am telling you?”<br>
<br>
Kalial nodded once and spoke in a small whisper.  “The new kingdom of Innoruuk has approached Neriak and demanded fealty.”<br>
<br>
